# Cursor IDE — entirely local to each developer. The rules under
# .cursor/rules/ contain internal workflow knowledge (filesystem paths,
# gh account names, release ritual minutiae) that we don't publish.
.cursor/

# Secrets / local-only configs
*.env
*.env.local
*.key
*.pem
*.local
*.local.*

# Apple signing material — private keys, certs, profiles. The App Store
# Connect API key (.p8) is downloadable exactly once. The Apple
# Distribution .p12 bundles a cert + its private key. Provisioning
# profiles encode team/app/cert linkage that we don't publish. Treat all
# of these like private keys.
*.p8
AuthKey_*.p8
*.p12
*.cer
*.p7b
*.mobileprovision
.appstore

# .ai-docs/ houses two classes of file:
#   1. Canonical public-ish docs that README.md links to and that
#      error messages in the GitHub workflows direct contributors at.
#      These need to be tracked — broken links on the public repo are
#      worse than the small leak of internal-feeling prose.
#   2. Internal planning / scratch notes — decision logs, security
#      planning, handoff context, business / LLC paperwork drafts, AI
#      sessions' working memory. These stay ignored. `feature_backlog.md`
#      lives here despite README mentions because it carries LLC EIN /
#      address / banking-vendor details that don't belong in public.
# Default: ignore everything; allow-list (`!`) only the canonical files.
.ai-docs/*
!.ai-docs/architecture.md
!.ai-docs/versioning.md
!.ai-docs/release_process.md
!.ai-docs/ios_device_signing.md
